# Wireshark: The Basics

**Room:** [TryHackMe – Wireshark: The Basics](https://tryhackme.com/room/wiresharkthebasics)
**Status:** Completed

## Summary
Introduced Wireshark's packet dissection model — breaking packets down
across OSI layers (Ethernet, IP, TCP, HTTP) — and how to inspect file
metadata and hashes via Capture File Properties.

## Key Concepts
- Packets are dissected layer-by-layer in the packet details pane;
  clicking a layer highlights its corresponding raw bytes in the hex view
- **Capture File Properties** exposes file hashes (SHA256, RIPEMD160,
  SHA1) for the .pcapng itself — useful for verifying capture integrity
  during evidence handling
- Demonstrated reading an HTTP GET request/response across the TCP
  stream reassembly
